Parliament, Tuesday, 27 February 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will this afternoon hold a hearing with the Department of Basic Education on matters relating to scholar transport. Details of the hearing: Date: Tuesday, 27 February 2018
	Time: 18:00
	Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI For media inquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
